Lucas Kanade/Pyramids:
Lucas Kanade is an optical flow algorithm which uses a differential method for detecting the motion of objects in consecutive images.
Key assumptions of lucas kanade is:
●	The core assumption of the lucas kanade algorithm is that the intensity of a feature/object does not significantly change between two consecutive frames. 
●	Another assumption of lucas kanade is that the objects that have been traced are not moving at high speed. Or we can say that lucas kanade best works on slow moving objects. 





These two equations fundamentally drive the algorithms.
Since for a given pixel we have two unknown (Vx and Vy) and only one variable, we bring another assumption.

We assume that optical flow(Vx and Vy vectors) are the same for a patch of points. This provides us with the given linear equations.






